        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         Zheart can be replaced by other, better items in the slot it has to be used in to give you it's effect. Plus, other items in the game can give you regen.. not to mention, buffs from other characters can give you pleanty of regen.</P><P>You will never find the ability to insta-invis yourself up from an FD. Ever, period. Yes, for a pre-nerf item, it's price is kinda low still.. but that's because there are still a lot. People realized the value on this one before it got nerfed and put a lot of them (by farming) into the economy. Eventually over time the price will go up as people leave their accounts with pre-nerf CoS's on them, and other players start new accounts without access to them (save for buying one).  Anyway, in time, the value goes up.. Guise of the Deciever, manastone, etc. (granted, manastone was nerfed so that it actually leveled off in price, but if Guise of the Deciever were droppable, it'd be going for insane amounts of plat at this date). </P><P>That's why people would rather sell their Zheart. Sure, it's a good item and semi-rare.. but you still have a chance at getting one, and it's usefulness is .. handy, at best. Pre-nerf CoS can mean the difference between 4 percent main level xp loss and laughing at mobs as you hop up from an FD invis only to run out of there.</P><P><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=205091" target="_blank"><font color=red><font size=5>Ashtaroth Solarium</font id=size5></font id=red></a><BR><i>Nec-Romancer of Innoruuk</i><BR><i>Legends of the Realm</i><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
